%spark.pyspark
names=['antenna_id','time','cdr_type','source','target','duration']
# Making the schema of the data
fields=[]
for header in names:
    fields.append(StructField(header, StringType(), False))
schema = StructType(fields)

df = sq.read.csv('s3n://sierra-leone-lake/blob/cdrs/africell-raw/20200201_1*.csv', schema=schema)

%spark.pyspark
# Get user with whom the record is associated
df = df.withColumn('direction', F.lower(F.split(df['cdr_type'], ' ').getItem(0)))
df = df.withColumn('user', F.when(df.direction=='incoming', df.target).otherwise(df.source))

#Get the date of the record
dated = df.withColumn('datetime', F.to_timestamp('time')).withColumn('date', F.to_date('datetime'))

# Drop unnecessary columns
dated = dated.drop('time', 'cdr_type', 'source', 'target', 'direction')

#Cast Duration to Integer
dated = dated.withColumn('duration', dated['duration'].cast('int').alias('duration'))
